              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "NGEN"
                ],
                "institute": "3CPRNPC"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " K-400 neutron generator"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The yield is about 5E10 n/4Pi/s. Solid tritium-",
                "titanium (T-Ti) target in thickness of 2.59 mg/cm2",
                "was bombarded by deuteron ions. The beam current of",
                "the deuterium was up to 180 uA with a maximum energy",
                "of 250 keV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "29-CU-65",
                "field_identifier": "NAT",
                "value": 0.3083
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Two natural copper and iron",
                "foils with a diameter of 15 mm and a thickness of",
                "0.1 mm were sandwiched between natural niobium foil",
                "and zirconium foil with the same diameter.",
                "The samples were placed at 40 and 60 deg angles",
                "relative to the deuteron beam direction and centered",
                "about the T-Ti target at a distance of about 4 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The copper samples were irradiated for about",
                "50 min, cooled for about 8 min each. The gamma-ray",
                "counting of reaction products in the irradiated",
                "samples was done for about 30 min each. The distance",
                "between the samples and the detector is 4.5 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " In order to monitor the variation of the",
                "neutron yield, accompanying alpha-particles were",
                "recorded every second during irradiation period by",
                "Au-Si surface barrier detector, which are placed at",
                "135 deg relative the direction of deuteron."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A series of point source (22Na, 60Co, 133Ba,",
                "137Cs, 152Eu, 210Pb, 241Am) of known activity were",
                "used to determine the absolute photopeak efficiency",
                "of a lead-shielded high purity germanium detector",
                "with a relative efficiency of 68% and an energy",
                "resolution of 1.82 keV at 1.33 MeV for 60Co."
              ]
            }
          ],
